OL,3,CHospices 'struggling with demand' to
OL,4,Creceive #4 million in extra funding
OL,6,FHospices in Wales will receive a share
OL,7,Fof #4 million from the , Health
OL,8,FSecretary Eluned Morgan has announced.
OL,10,FIt will be shared across 12 adult and
OL,11,Fchildren's hospices in Wales to help
OL,12,Fthem maintain services, meet staffing
OL,13,Fcosts and improve the quality of end-
OL,14,Fof-life care. The funding is part of a
OL,15,Freview into end-of-life care in Wales.
OL,17,FMore than #770,000 will be given to
OL,18,Fchildren's hospices Ty Gobaith and Ty
OL,19,FHafan which support children and young
OL,20,Fpeople living with a life-limiting
OL,21,Fcondition.
